headline: US stocks fall to their first loss in 6 days as bitcoin tumbles
summary: The S&P 500 slipped 0.5% and broke a five-day winning streak.  The Dow Jones Industrial Average dropped 427 points, or 0.9%, and the Nasdaq composite dipped 0.4%.  Last week’s rally was largely due to rising hopes  that the Federal Reserve will cut  its main interest rate next week to help shore up the slowing job market.
